849
01:32:05,319 --> 01:32:13,103
♪ I'm only going over Jordan ♪

850
01:32:13,127 --> 01:32:21,127
♪ I'm only going over home. ♪

851
01:32:25,707 --> 01:32:28,452
D Company, move out!

852
01:32:28,476 --> 01:32:30,521
You all right, pal?

853
01:32:30,545 --> 01:32:32,155
Uh, where you from?

854
01:32:32,179 --> 01:32:33,424
He's probably got the wind up.

855
01:32:33,448 --> 01:32:34,559
Well, he's not one of ours.

856
01:32:34,583 --> 01:32:36,460
He's bloody soaked.

857
01:32:36,484 --> 01:32:39,296
Fuck it. Let's just pick
him up and take him with us.

858
01:32:39,320 --> 01:32:41,699
Have to find the Devons.

859
01:32:41,723 --> 01:32:44,602
- What's he saying?
- What's that, mate?

860
01:32:44,626 --> 01:32:46,737
The Devons.

861
01:32:46,761 --> 01:32:50,408
I have to find the Devons.

862
01:32:50,432 --> 01:32:52,432
We're the Devons.

863
01:32:55,704 --> 01:32:58,238
- You're the Devons?
- Yes, Corp.

864
01:33:00,274 --> 01:33:01,686
Why haven't you gone over?

865
01:33:01,710 --> 01:33:03,353
W-We're the second wave.

866
01:33:03,377 --> 01:33:05,188
They don't send us all at once.

867
01:33:05,212 --> 01:33:08,191
Yeah, we're D Company.
We spent the night digging in.

868
01:33:08,215 --> 01:33:09,716
We go last.

869
01:33:11,486 --> 01:33:13,163
Are you all right?

870
01:33:13,187 --> 01:33:15,533
Mackenzie.
Where's Colonel Mackenzie?

871
01:33:15,557 --> 01:33:17,635
Well, he's down at the line.

872
01:33:17,659 --> 01:33:19,269
- Which way?
- This way.

873
01:33:19,293 --> 01:33:21,371
We're headed up there now.

874
01:33:21,395 --> 01:33:23,395
Oy, steady on, mate.
Where you going?

875
01:33:44,719 --> 01:33:46,286
Move!

876
01:33:49,824 --> 01:33:51,526
Let me by!

877
01:33:55,396 --> 01:33:56,707
Let me through!

878
01:33:56,731 --> 01:34:00,978
Remember, follow
your platoon commander.

879
01:34:01,002 --> 01:34:03,714
Stay spread out
and watch for his orders.

880
01:34:03,738 --> 01:34:05,516
Where is
your commanding officer?

881
01:34:05,540 --> 01:34:07,317
He's in the holding pen.

882
01:34:07,341 --> 01:34:10,788
Raise your signal
flags or fire the signal flares

883
01:34:10,812 --> 01:34:13,424
when you've taken your section
of the Hun line.

884
01:34:13,448 --> 01:34:14,692
B Company, stand to.

885
01:34:14,716 --> 01:34:16,594
Now, listen and listen well.

886
01:34:16,618 --> 01:34:18,663
On the first mark,
A Company will advance.

887
01:34:18,687 --> 01:34:20,831
B Company will then move
to the front line.

888
01:34:20,855 --> 01:34:23,000
Sir, I have a message
from General Erinmore.

889
01:34:23,024 --> 01:34:24,367
Who the fuck are you?

890
01:34:24,391 --> 01:34:25,736
The attack has been called off.

891
01:34:25,760 --> 01:34:27,705
General Erinmore has
called off the attack.

892
01:34:27,729 --> 01:34:29,707
Balls, man.
We're about to go over.

893
01:34:29,731 --> 01:34:31,442
- We've got them on the run.
- You don't.

894
01:34:31,466 --> 01:34:32,576
Please don't send your men over.

895
01:34:32,600 --> 01:34:33,844
Get out of the way, Corporal!

896
01:34:33,868 --> 01:34:35,479
These are direct orders
from army command!

897
01:34:35,503 --> 01:34:36,714
Where is Colonel Mackenzie?!

898
01:34:36,738 --> 01:34:39,617
Jesus Christ, man!
Go and see the captain!

899
01:34:39,641 --> 01:34:41,719
Now, I want us up there
quickly, you understand?

900
01:34:41,743 --> 01:34:43,454
Do you understand?!

901
01:34:43,478 --> 01:34:45,723
- Yes, sir!
- Two Mills bombs per man.

902
01:34:45,747 --> 01:34:48,324
NCOs collect flares
and signal flags.

903
01:34:48,348 --> 01:34:50,317
- Keep to your stations.
- Oy. Oy!

904
01:34:58,560 --> 01:35:01,605
Nine and ten section
at the ready!

905
01:35:01,629 --> 01:35:05,476
We will advance
on the first whistle blast.

906
01:35:05,500 --> 01:35:07,377
- 11 and 12...
- not slow down.

907
01:35:07,401 --> 01:35:09,680
The man next to you falls,
keep moving.

908
01:35:09,704 --> 01:35:11,716
Your orders are
to break the lines.

909
01:35:11,740 --> 01:35:13,349
Where is the captain?

910
01:35:13,373 --> 01:35:15,385
He's over there.

911
01:35:15,409 --> 01:35:16,654
Keep in your section formation.

912
01:35:16,678 --> 01:35:18,622
Sir! Sir!

913
01:35:18,646 --> 01:35:21,892
Captain, I have a message.

914
01:35:21,916 --> 01:35:23,894
This attack is called off.

915
01:35:23,918 --> 01:35:26,488
You have to stop.
You have to stop!

916
01:35:30,424 --> 01:35:32,368
Where is Colonel Mackenzie?

917
01:35:32,392 --> 01:35:34,361
Where is Mackenzie?!

918
01:36:01,589 --> 01:36:03,333
Get back! Back!

919
01:36:03,357 --> 01:36:05,102
Return to your sections! Back!

920
01:36:05,126 --> 01:36:06,670
Hold fast!

921
01:36:06,694 --> 01:36:08,806
Seven Platoon, one minute!

922
01:36:08,830 --> 01:36:12,409
Sir, I have orders
to stop this attack!

923
01:36:12,433 --> 01:36:13,444
What?

924
01:36:13,468 --> 01:36:15,679
Where is Colonel Mackenzie?!

925
01:36:15,703 --> 01:36:17,648
He's further up the line.

926
01:36:17,672 --> 01:36:19,416
- How far?
- 300 yards.

927
01:36:19,440 --> 01:36:21,118
He's in a cut-and-cover.

928
01:36:21,142 --> 01:36:23,821
You'll have to wait until
the first wave goes over.

929
01:36:23,845 --> 01:36:25,780
No. No, I can't.

930
01:36:33,655 --> 01:36:36,858
Seven Platoon, 30 seconds!

931
01:36:48,837 --> 01:36:50,714
You can't possibly
make it that way, man.

932
01:36:50,738 --> 01:36:52,674
Are you bloody insane?

933
01:36:56,678 --> 01:36:59,423
What the hell are you doing,
Lance Corporal?

934
01:36:59,447 --> 01:37:01,516
No. No, no, no, no!

935
01:38:03,611 --> 01:38:05,789
Into position!

936
01:38:05,813 --> 01:38:07,524
Get ready!

937
01:38:07,548 --> 01:38:09,784
- Colonel Mackenzie.
- He's in there.

938
01:38:11,552 --> 01:38:13,864
- Two minutes!
- Let me through!

939
01:38:13,888 --> 01:38:15,666
Hey. Hey!

940
01:38:15,690 --> 01:38:17,468
- Let me through!
- What the hell do you think you're doing?

941
01:38:17,492 --> 01:38:18,636
I have to get through!

942
01:38:18,660 --> 01:38:20,004
I have to see Colonel Mackenzie.

943
01:38:20,028 --> 01:38:21,739
- What are you doing?
- I have to stop this attack.

944
01:38:21,763 --> 01:38:22,973
Colonel, we've seen flares.

945
01:38:22,997 --> 01:38:25,542
The men on the left flank have
made it to the German line.

946
01:38:25,566 --> 01:38:27,678
- Colonel! Colonel!
- Hold him. Hold him.

947
01:38:27,702 --> 01:38:29,914
Listen to me. Listen to me.
I have a letter.

948
01:38:29,938 --> 01:38:31,749
I need to see Colonel Mackenzie!

949
01:38:31,773 --> 01:38:33,684
There's no bloody way
you're getting in there, mate.

950
01:38:33,708 --> 01:38:34,818
Sergeant, send the next wave.

951
01:38:34,842 --> 01:38:36,487
No!

952
01:38:36,511 --> 01:38:38,589
Second wave, prepare yourselves!

953
01:38:38,613 --> 01:38:40,591
- Colonel Mackenzie!
- Concentrate everything there.

954
01:38:40,615 --> 01:38:42,693
This attack is not to go ahead!

955
01:38:42,717 --> 01:38:45,696
You have been ordered to stop.
You have to stop.

956
01:38:45,720 --> 01:38:47,564
Who the hell are you?

957
01:38:47,588 --> 01:38:49,833
Lance Corporal Schofield,
sir, 8th.

958
01:38:49,857 --> 01:38:51,568
I have orders from
General Erinmore

959
01:38:51,592 --> 01:38:52,703
to call off this attack.

960
01:38:52,727 --> 01:38:54,071
You're too late, Lance Corporal.

961
01:38:54,095 --> 01:38:56,106
Sir, these orders
are from army command.

962
01:38:56,130 --> 01:38:57,708
You have to read them.

963
01:38:57,732 --> 01:38:59,510
Shall we hold back
the second wave, sir?

964
01:38:59,534 --> 01:39:00,811
No, Major.
Hesitate now, and we lose.

965
01:39:00,835 --> 01:39:02,579
Victory's only 500 yards away.

966
01:39:02,603 --> 01:39:04,515
Sir, please read the letter.

967
01:39:04,539 --> 01:39:07,518
I have heard it all before.

968
01:39:07,542 --> 01:39:09,586
I'm not going to wait
until dusk or for fog.

969
01:39:09,610 --> 01:39:10,888
I'm not calling back my men

970
01:39:10,912 --> 01:39:12,556
only to send them
out there again tomorrow,

971
01:39:12,580 --> 01:39:13,958
not when we've got
the bastards on the run.

972
01:39:13,982 --> 01:39:15,592
This is their last stand.

973
01:39:15,616 --> 01:39:18,028
The Germans planned this, sir.

974
01:39:18,052 --> 01:39:19,830
They've been planning it
for months.

975
01:39:19,854 --> 01:39:22,733
They want you to attack.

976
01:39:22,757 --> 01:39:24,692
Read the letter.

977
01:39:44,645 --> 01:39:46,614
- Major?
- Yes, sir?

978
01:39:48,916 --> 01:39:51,628
- Stand them down.
- Yes, sir.

979
01:39:51,652 --> 01:39:53,764
Call up the
orderlies. Tend the wounded.

980
01:39:53,788 --> 01:39:55,566
Hold the line
in case they counter.

981
01:39:55,590 --> 01:39:57,001
Yes, sir.

982
01:39:57,025 --> 01:40:00,626
Stand down! Stand down!

983
01:40:02,363 --> 01:40:03,696
Stand down!

984
01:40:05,833 --> 01:40:09,035
- Cease fire! Cease fire!
- Stand down!

985
01:40:13,074 --> 01:40:15,676
I hoped today might be
a good day.

986
01:40:17,945 --> 01:40:20,148
Hope is a dangerous thing.

987
01:40:21,883 --> 01:40:23,761
That's it for now,
and then next week,

988
01:40:23,785 --> 01:40:26,797
command will send
a different message.

989
01:40:26,821 --> 01:40:28,756
"Attack at dawn."

990
01:40:31,859 --> 01:40:33,961
There is only one way
this war ends.

991
01:40:36,397 --> 01:40:38,566
Last man standing.

992
01:40:43,838 --> 01:40:45,807
Have someone see to your wounds.

993
01:40:48,709 --> 01:40:50,945
Now fuck off, Lance Corporal.

994
01:40:56,717 --> 01:40:57,895
Bearers!

995
01:40:57,919 --> 01:41:00,864
Stretcher bearers!

996
01:41:00,888 --> 01:41:02,633
Bearers!

997
01:41:02,657 --> 01:41:04,635
Stretcher bearers!

998
01:41:04,659 --> 01:41:07,037
Well done, lad.

999
01:41:07,061 --> 01:41:08,729
Thank you, sir.

1000
01:41:10,798 --> 01:41:13,043
Do you know where
Lieutenant Blake is, sir?

1001
01:41:13,067 --> 01:41:14,845
Blake?

1002
01:41:14,869 --> 01:41:16,747
There were two of us.

1003
01:41:16,771 --> 01:41:19,049
I was sent here
with his brother.

1004
01:41:19,073 --> 01:41:21,118
Ah.

1005
01:41:21,142 --> 01:41:22,920
Well, knowing Lieutenant Blake,

1006
01:41:22,944 --> 01:41:24,855
he would have gone over
with his men.

1007
01:41:24,879 --> 01:41:27,991
He was in the first wave.

1008
01:41:28,015 --> 01:41:29,860
How could I find him, sir?

1009
01:41:29,884 --> 01:41:32,062
You can try
the casualty clearing station

1010
01:41:32,086 --> 01:41:34,932
behind the line.

1011
01:41:34,956 --> 01:41:36,657
Otherwise...

1012
01:41:39,727 --> 01:41:41,138
Thank you, sir.

1013
01:41:41,162 --> 01:41:43,162
Major Hepburn, sir.

1014
01:41:50,938 --> 01:41:52,907
- Keep moving. Keep moving.
- Nearly there.

1015
01:42:03,718 --> 01:42:05,052
Ow!

1016
01:42:07,755 --> 01:42:08,823
Will I make it?

1017
01:42:11,125 --> 01:42:12,960
Will I make it?

1018
01:42:17,165 --> 01:42:19,810
- Go the fuck up.
- Clear the way.

1019
01:42:19,834 --> 01:42:21,245
Come on, quickly.

1020
01:42:21,269 --> 01:42:23,247
Get a medic!

1021
01:42:23,271 --> 01:42:26,807
Medic! Medic!

1022
01:42:34,148 --> 01:42:35,225
Just keep moving.

1023
01:42:35,249 --> 01:42:37,161
Keep moving, keep moving.

1024
01:42:37,185 --> 01:42:38,951
That's it.

1025
01:43:02,777 --> 01:43:05,022
Sergeant, I have to find
Lieutenant Blake.

1026
01:43:05,046 --> 01:43:06,981
- Do you know where he is?
- No.

1027
01:43:11,786 --> 01:43:13,096
Make way for the stretchers!

1028
01:43:13,120 --> 01:43:14,798
Minor injuries to the far field.

1029
01:43:14,822 --> 01:43:16,233
Stretchers to me.

1030
01:43:16,257 --> 01:43:18,835
Walking wounded
to the collection area.

1031
01:43:18,859 --> 01:43:21,260
Move aside to let
the stretcher bearers through.

1032
01:43:25,833 --> 01:43:27,768
- Move it.
- Clear the way.

1033
01:43:28,903 --> 01:43:31,048
Sir, is Lieutenant Blake here?

1034
01:43:31,072 --> 01:43:33,317
No idea.

1035
01:43:33,341 --> 01:43:36,253
Move along, Corporal.

1036
01:43:36,277 --> 01:43:39,056
If you can walk,
move to the triage area.

1037
01:43:39,080 --> 01:43:40,857
I can't move.

1038
01:43:40,881 --> 01:43:42,083
Help me.

1039
01:43:44,852 --> 01:43:46,096
Let me go home.

1040
01:43:46,120 --> 01:43:47,364
Lieutenant Blake!

1041
01:43:47,388 --> 01:43:49,323
I need an M.O. over here.

1042
01:43:52,827 --> 01:43:54,204
Sir, he's out.

1043
01:43:54,228 --> 01:43:57,007
Get him out of here, now.

1044
01:43:57,031 --> 01:44:00,077
Out of the bloody way.

1045
01:44:00,101 --> 01:44:02,212
Blake?!

1046
01:44:02,236 --> 01:44:03,880
Out of the way!

1047
01:44:03,904 --> 01:44:05,973
Has anyone seen
Lieutenant Blake?!

1048
01:44:07,875 --> 01:44:08,986
He's hemorrhaging.
Go quickly.

1049
01:44:09,010 --> 01:44:10,988
He needs a surgeon.

1050
01:44:11,012 --> 01:44:14,024
I want to be left here.

1051
01:44:14,048 --> 01:44:16,393
Tourniquet!

1052
01:44:16,417 --> 01:44:18,295
- Don't look. It's okay.
- Amputation.

1053
01:44:18,319 --> 01:44:20,219
Straight to surgery.

1054
01:44:22,056 --> 01:44:25,259
My leg! My leg.

1055
01:44:28,396 --> 01:44:30,307
I need some help here, quickly!

1056
01:44:30,331 --> 01:44:31,908
He's gone.

1057
01:44:31,932 --> 01:44:34,177
I can't die.

1058
01:44:34,201 --> 01:44:36,179
Don't let me fucking die.

1059
01:44:36,203 --> 01:44:38,339
- I need something now!
- I need my mum.

1060
01:44:41,042 --> 01:44:42,243
Coming through.

1061
01:44:56,190 --> 01:44:58,302
All right, come on, boys.

1062
01:44:58,326 --> 01:45:00,203
He's taken one in the leg.

1063
01:45:00,227 --> 01:45:02,205
- He's lost a lot of blood.
- Sir.

1064
01:45:02,229 --> 01:45:03,641
Lieutenant Blake?

1065
01:45:03,665 --> 01:45:06,276
Yes?

1066
01:45:06,300 --> 01:45:09,346
Do you need medical assistance?

1067
01:45:09,370 --> 01:45:11,148
No, sir.

1068
01:45:11,172 --> 01:45:12,450
I'm from the 8th.

1069
01:45:12,474 --> 01:45:15,085
What the hell
are you doing here?

1070
01:45:15,109 --> 01:45:16,953
I was sent here
to deliver a message.

1071
01:45:16,977 --> 01:45:18,155
The 8th?

1072
01:45:18,179 --> 01:45:20,924
You must know my brother.

1073
01:45:20,948 --> 01:45:22,259
I was sent here with him.

1074
01:45:22,283 --> 01:45:24,251
Tom's here? Where is he?

1075
01:45:30,525 --> 01:45:32,461
It was very quick.

1076
01:45:34,529 --> 01:45:36,230
I'm sorry.

1077
01:46:00,087 --> 01:46:02,199
What's your name?

1078
01:46:02,223 --> 01:46:04,158
Schofield, sir.

1079
01:46:07,027 --> 01:46:09,072
I'm sorry, what?

1080
01:46:09,096 --> 01:46:10,941
It's Schofield, sir.

1081
01:46:10,965 --> 01:46:13,377
William Schofield.

1082
01:46:13,401 --> 01:46:14,969
Will.

1083
01:46:17,037 --> 01:46:18,382
Well, you need some food.

1084
01:46:18,406 --> 01:46:20,341
Get yourself to the mess tent.

1085
01:46:35,122 --> 01:46:40,003
If I may, I'd like
to write to your mother.

1086
01:46:40,027 --> 01:46:41,962
Tell her that Tom wasn't alone.

1087
01:46:44,599 --> 01:46:46,535
Of course.

1088
01:46:49,236 --> 01:46:52,048
He was...

1089
01:46:52,072 --> 01:46:53,941
He was a good man.

1090
01:46:55,777 --> 01:46:57,945
Always telling funny stories.

1091
01:47:00,482 --> 01:47:02,451
He saved my life.

1092
01:47:06,220 --> 01:47:08,189
I am glad you were with him.

1093
01:47:14,228 --> 01:47:16,163
Thank you, Will.

